added.title: Beast Boy on a Shelf
added.description: Santa Claus forces Beast Boy to become a spy and report on the Titans' naughty behavior.

added.title: Christmas Crusaders
added.description: Santa Claus and Robin must stop the nefarious Coal Miner.

added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.title: Teen Titans Save Christmas
added.description: Santa calls it quits so the Titans must pitch in to save the holiday.

added.title: The True Meaning of Christmas
added.description: Fed up with never getting presents from Santa, the Titans head to the north pole to take themselves off the Naughty List by any means necessary.

added.title: Second Christmas
added.description: The Titans trick Starfire into believing in second Christmas with second Santa.

added.title: The Re-Run
added.description: When we last saw Gumball, he was hitting rewind on Rob's Universal Remote just in time to save himself from being trapped in The Void. The remote has now taken Gumball back to the beginning of that disastrous day. Armed with the knowledge of what this day has in store, he must try and stop Rob from destroying his life.

added.title: The Guy
added.description: Gumball and Darwin put Anais' new friend, Josh, through a series of tests, to see if he's good enough for their sister. However, when the boys' extreme methods start freaking Josh out, he questions whether being Anais's friend is worth the trouble. So Gumball and Darwin end up having to convince Josh to give Anais a second chance.

added.title: The Boredom
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are convinced it's one of those days when nothing interesting is happening. But as they walk around Elmore in search of adventure, it becomes apparent exciting things are happening just not to them.

added.title: The Vision
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin accidentally find a sinister secret manifesto on Alan's memory stick, they decide they have to foil his plan for total world domination. As the fantasy of Alan's new world order spins out of control, Gumball and Darwin resort to desperate measures.

added.title: The Choices
added.description: When a typically stressful Watterson family dinner pushes her to the edge of her sanity, Nicole starts reminiscing about the time she met Richard. Might her life have been better if she'd never stopped to talk to her future husband and taken a different path instead?

added.title: The Code
added.description: Gumball learns the Wattersons have been stealing Mr. Robinson's wi-fi for years. When it goes down, they try and live without it but life offline proves too hard. Gumball and Darwin decide to hack their way through cyberspace to learn Mr Robinson's passcode.

added.title: The Scam
added.description: At Halloween show and tell, the class isn't buying Gumball's story about Gargaroth the Devourer until Carrie fakes a terrifying haunting. The kids convince the school to hire them as ghost exterminators and take their payment in Halloween candy. But when it turns out Gargaroth is real, suddenly Gumball is expected to be the town's savior.

added.title: The Test
added.description: Gumball is livid when an online test keeps telling him that his character-type is "The Loser". He's convinced the only way to shake off this label is to do the opposite of everything he normally would. But Gumball suppressing his natural instincts leaves a vacuum, a Gumball-shaped hole that someone has to fill. That someone is Tobias, who starts turning the whole show into a cliched sitcom.

added.title: The Slide
added.description: A chance encounter with the woman of his dreams inspires Rocky to stop living life online and find love with the help of the latest dating app. Gumball and Darwin try to help Rocky through the tricky world of online romance. In the race to find Rocky's dream girl, they discover people can forgive almost anything when you tell them you're acting in the name of love.

added.title: The Loophole
added.description: Gumball and Darwin give Bobert specific instructions to ensure he acts in a safe and responsible manner. When Bobert starts applying his robot logic to their rules, they soon realize they're going to have to be much clearer. Or he will end up destroying them all.

added.title: The Copycats
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are confused when they meet Kiki and Quack, a pair of siblings that copy everything they do and say. Then they find out this copycat family is making money online from imitating the Watterson family! When they fail to encourage them to find their own identity, the Wattersons realize they need a more permanent solution.

added.title: The Potato
added.description: When Darwin has lunch with Idaho, he decides to stop eating potatoes in solidarity with his brotato. However, he finds his obsession with his favourite food harder to kick than he ever imagined so Gumball decides to help his friend curb his carb cravings.

added.title: The Fuss
added.description: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else!

added.title: Christmas
added.description: Santa Claus is coming to town. Unfortunately he gets run over by the Wattersons, so it's up to them to save Christmas.

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Craig and his friends desperately want a Snow Day, so they turn to the most powerful people they know... The Witches of the Creek!

added.title: Winter Break
added.description: Craig returns to the Creek after the long Winter Break only to find an empty wasteland and danger lurking in the snow.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: While taking refuge from the chilly Creek, Craig and his friends decide to hangout at his house until lunch time!

added.title: Breaking the Ice
added.description: While searching a once unreachable part of the Creek, Craig gets stranded with his longtime rival, Wildernessa!

added.title: Winter Creeklympics
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP try their luck at winning Gold in their first ever, Winter Creeklympics!

added.title: Capture The Flag Part I
added.description: When mysterious circumstances cause issues at the Trading Tree, Craig tries to save the day!

added.title: Capture The Flag Part II
added.description: The Creek gets help from an unlikely friend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part III
added.description: Craig goes in search of answers, and finds a legend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part IV
added.description: Craig puts a plan into motion to save the Creek.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part V
added.description: It all comes down to this, the fate of the Creek is at stake!

added.title: Bug City Sleuths
added.description: To survive in a city inhabited by bugs, the Bears become noir-style detectives.

added.title: Hashtag #1 Fan
added.description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

added.title: Back to Our Regular Time Period
added.description: The Bears find themselves trapped in the wrong time period.

added.title: Bath on the Nile
added.description: The Bears find themselves in an ancient Egyptian spa, but Grizz refuses to take a bath.

added.title: Duncan Carving
added.description: Duncan takes advantage of a questionable Halloween legend to steal candy from his classmates.

added.title: Gobble Head
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Tiger Fail
added.description: Gwen refuses to be pressured into choosing an ice cream flavor that she does not want.

added.title: A Ninjustice to Harold
added.description: Harold's world is turned upside down when Beth becomes the class ninja.

added.title: Having the Timeout of Our Lives
added.description: Owen forms a special bond with Duncan after having loads of fun with him during their timeouts.

added.title: Hole In Roof
added.description: Suddenly the hole in the roof is no longer a laughing matter but one of a life or death.

added.title: Patty's Law
added.description: If found guilty of breaking Patty's Law, Apple and Onion face grave punishment but they have a more pressing concern; looking after their dear, sickly Falafel.

added.title: Apple & Onion's Booth
added.description: Apple and Onion must save their favorite booth at Pizza's Diner from a Texas oil tycoon.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

added.title: Pat on the Head
added.description: Apple and Onion are to cook for a very important guest but Onion is not quite feeling himself.

added.title: Falafel's Glory
added.description: Apple and Onion must recruit the help of retired quiz master Falafel if they are to not starve.

added.title: Christmas Spirit
added.description: Apple & Onion know exactly what gifts they want this Christmas but all their money has been squandered. Luckily they find a suitably festive way to make back that money.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

added.title: Microwave's Dance Club
added.description: DJ Saltfish and MC Ackee are in town for two nights only and Apple and Onion are determined to make the most of it and bust some moves on the dance floor.

added.title: All Work and No Play
added.description: Having finally saved up and aquired an expensive toy race track, Apple and Onion are faced with one problem- there is no time to play with it.

added.title: Drone Shoes
added.description: Can there exist such a thing as drone shoes? It sounds like they would need a huge power capacity.

added.title: Walking on the Ceiling
added.description: Apple's curiosity of what it would be like to walk upside down like a spider should be ignored and given no further thought. It is not.

added.title: Keep It Fresh
added.description: It's Apple's turn to buy this months' groceries again meaning that the risk of starvation is at hand.

added.title: Panamanian Night Monkey
added.description: Apple and Onion must adopt unorthodox measures if they are to see this special animal at the zoo.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Historical Friction
added.description: Steven and Jamie put on a play about the founding of Beach City.

added.title: Friend Ship
added.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: When Ben, as Upgrade, and Gwen get zapped into a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben soon has to deal with Gwen's superior gaming skills, while he also tries to impress his video icon in the game.

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: Super Alien Hero Buddy Adventures
added.description: Ben discovers his alien heroes have been ripped off by a lame cartoon and he is not happy. So he sets out to make things right.

added.title: Stuck on You
added.description: Kybher, aided by a booger-like slime biot named Skurd, attacks Ben & co, but the tables turn when Skurd gloms onto Ben!

added.title: Let's Do the Time War Again
added.description: Ben, Skurd and Rook find themselves caught in an endless time loop as enemies from the future converge on Bellwood.

added.title: The Secret of Dos Santos
added.description: Ben and Rook join Kai Green on a perilous alien relic hunt through South America.

added.title: Third Time's a Charm
added.description: Charmaster returns to exact her revenge on Gwendolyn once and for all.

added.title: The Final Countdown
added.description: Rook and his little Plumbers must defend the Base from a mysterious lockdown.

added.title: Christmas Movies
added.description: On Christmas Eve, the Baby Bears defend a video store from getting robbed.

added.title: The Perfect Tree
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear drive up north to find the perfect Christmas tree. Meanwhile, Grizz and Panda are in charge of decorating Chloe's house.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Ranger Tabes
added.description: To recover a missing package, the Bears get help from Ranger Tabes, an eccentric forest ranger. But her overblown sense of justice might be too much for the Bears to handle.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Christmas Parties
added.description: The Bears have been invited to all their friends' Christmas parties. In an effort to have time to crash Nom Nom's huge star-studded bash, the Bears first try to make quick stops at all their friends' parties throughout the night.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: My Clique
added.description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

added.title: Nuthin' Special/Neighbor Hood
added.description: Nuthing Special: Frustrated with not knowing what her special power is, Buttercup hunts to discover what makes her special./Neighbor Hood: When everyone on Bubbles' favorite show loses their happy, Bubbles helps bring it back.

added.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea?: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: I See a Funny Cartoon in Your Future/Octi-Gone
added.description: I See a Funny Cartoon In Your Future: The girls have the rare task of fighting a medium who is committing petty thefts./Octi-gone: When Bubbles finds a single leg of Octi's, she sets out to find out who took her toy and what they want from her.

added.title: Little Miss Interprets/Night Mayor
added.description: Little Miss Interprets: When the girls hear the Professor trying to make something out of sugar, spice and everything nice, they are sure he's trying to create new little girls./Night Mayor: The Mayor keeps having the same dream over and over again but he never sees the end. Now, it's up the girls to go into the Mayor's head and solve this mystery.

added.title: The Gift
added.description: The girls must replace the Professor's Christmas present on Christmas Eve.

added.title: The Last Donnycorn
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

added.title: Green Wing
added.description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

added.title: 15 Minutes of Fame
added.description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Clawdad
added.description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: A Star is Blossom
added.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

added.title: Mini Golf Madness
added.description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

added.title: Summer Bummer
added.description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

added.title: You're a Good Man, Mojo Jojo
added.description: The holidays are Mojo's favorite time…for ruining everything! But this year, he may just learn the reason for the season.

added.title: Snow Month
added.description: After a snow day saves Blossom from having to face a boy who's asked her out, she decides to use her ice breath to keep it going even if that means plunging Townsville into eternal winter complete with monstrous yetis!

added.title: Elements Part 1: Skyhooks
added.description: Upon returning to Ooo, Finn and Jake discover that there have been some radical changes in their absence.

added.title: Elements Part 2: Bespoken For
added.description: Ice King weaves a tale filled with drama, romance, and men's fashion.

added.title: Elements Part 3: Winter Light
added.description: Finn, Jake, and Ice King travel to the new Ice Kingdom to confront the person responsible for turning everything topsy-turvy.

added.title: Islands Part 1: The Invitation
added.description: A mysterious craft invades Ooo and Finn believes it may hold the secrets to his past.

added.title: Islands Part 2: Whipple the Happy Dragon
added.description: Finn, Jake, and Susan set sail on a ocean voyage full of wonders and danger.

added.title: Islands Part 3: Mysterious Island
added.description: After waking up alone and shipwrecked, Finn investigates a bizarre island in search of his friends.

added.title: Islands Part 4: Imaginary Resources
added.description: Finn and Jake travel to a land where reality has been redesigned and improved.

added.title: Islands Part 5: Hide and Seek
added.description: While exploring some futuristic ruins, Susan sees glimpses of a familiar girl.

added.title: Islands Part 6: Min & Marty
added.description: An unexpected revelation from Susan leads Finn closer to answers about his past.

added.title: Islands Part 7: Helpers
added.description: Finn and his friends journey to a last refuge called Founders Island.

added.title: Islands Part 8: The Light Cloud
added.description: Finn confronts the power behind Founders Island, but will he ever return home to Ooo?

added.title: The More You Moe, the Moe You Know
added.description: Moe visits the tree house with a special birthday surprise for BMO. While BMO's mission stands on the brink of disaster, Finn & Jake host a strange guest.

added.title: Holly Jolly Secrets
added.description: Finn and Jake continue to explore the world of old Christmas specials while the Ice King fumes.

added.title: Space Escape
added.description: The guys have to escape from someone bad.

added.title: New Beds
added.description: The guys get new beds.

added.title: Mordeby and Rigbecai
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby mess around with a teleportation machine, and you can pretty much imagine how this one goes.

added.title: Alpha Dome
added.description: The guys confront some people.

added.title: Christmas in Space
added.description: The guys celebrate their first Christmas in space by opening presents, eating peppermint bark and telling Christmas stories. Benson wants the stories to be more Christmas-y but the guys keep adding scary elements, which only infuriate their boss.

added.title: Snow Tubing
added.description: Rigby wants Eileen to go snow tubing.

added.title: White Elephant Gift Exchange
added.description: The park guys want revenge on Muscle Man for all his terrible gifts.

added.title: Merry Christmas Mordecai
added.description: Mordecai has to get through a Christmas party with C.J. without messing everything up.

added.title: New Year's Kiss
added.description: Rigby has to stop Mordecai from kissing a girl on New Year's Eve.

added.title: The Christmas Special
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to destroy a gift for Santa to save Christmas.

added.title: Merry Moochmas
added.description: It's wintertime in Aberdale and Clarence is convinced his winter wish for snow in Arizona will come true! However, his classmate Belson along with his grumpy cousin Gary Mooch are a little tougher to convince.

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Field Trippin'
added.description: After a pit stop bathroom break during a school field trip, Clarence returns to the parking lot and accidentally gets on the wrong school bus - which takes him to a different school!

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Doctor Visit
added.description: Uncle Grandpa hates going to the doctor but he's overdue for an important vaccination.

added.title: The Cake Mistake
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus eat a cake meant for someone else.

added.title: Sheep Deprivation
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid who can't fall asleep.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: Surprise Party
added.description: Mr. Gus and Belly Bag are throwing a surprise party for Pizza Steve, as long as  Uncle Grandpa doesn't spoil their surprise.

added.title: Late Night Good Morning With Uncle Grandpa
added.description: It's the Late Night Good Morning show with your host, Uncle Grandpa!

added.title: New Direction
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the best directors in the business help a kid in need of acting lessons become a star.

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: Aunt Grandma's back is causing more trouble for Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Secret Santa
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and the crew all have the same popular and hard-to-find gift in mine for their Secret Santa, their nice Christmas shopping trip to the mall turns into a crazy competition.

added.title: UG Christmas Special
added.description: Santa and Uncle Grandpa must work through their personal differences order to save Christmas.

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Crushing Defeat
added.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Top of the Naughty List
added.description: It's Christmas Eve and Brock is excited for Santa to come and visit as he settles down for a bedtime story from Master Frown, Unikitty and gang burst in. They are there to stop Master Frown from ruining any more Christmases. Frown pleads innocent but Unikitty and the gang tell the stories of the past Christmases he has already ruined.  Will Frown prove his innocence or will he rocket to the top of the Naughty List?

added.title: System Error
added.description: When Batman discovers that he and the rest of the League are robots, he investigates to find out who did this and why?

added.title: Race Against Crime
added.description: Superman and Flash race for charity only to fall under a trap perpetrated by Luthor, who has devised a "time" suit that allows him to control everyone's speed.

added.title: Party Animal
added.description: Green Arrow, who is determined to finally throw a successful holiday party for the Justice League, finds his plans thwarted when Plastic Man brings a tranquilized super villain to the gathering.

added.title: Watchtower Tours
added.description: When Booster Gold starts to secretly give tours of the Watchtower to make some extra cash, he inadvertently brings in a super villain disguised as a tourist.

added.title: Barehanded
added.description: When Green Lantern leaves his ring in an intergalactic restroom after washing his hands, he discovers it's gone, leading him on a wild chase for the aliens who might have taken it.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: A Real Steal/Lightning Unleashed
added.description: A Real Steal: Dan embarks on a solo adventure to outdo Magnus's new team of Bakugan Brawlers and winds up having to be saved by them instead./Lightning Unleashed: Lightning uncovers the Mind Core Cell buried beneath the Earth and battles Stata the Hunter in an effort to protect its secret.

added.title: The Throw Down/Brawl for It All
added.description: The Throw Down: Lightning reveals his discovery of the Mind Core Cell but the AO arrive only to discover that Magnus has already beaten them to it./Brawl for It All: With both team's Bakugan knocked into a hibernation state by the Mind Core Cell only Dan and Magnus remain locked in a brawl for it all!

added.title: Career Opportunities/Punch the Clock
added.description: Career Opportunities: After defeating Magnus the AO get an offer of employment from a surprising source Philomena Dusk!/Punch the Clock: During a commercial to celebrate their joining the AAAnimus team Dan and the AO rebel before they sellout.

added.title: High Flying Hostiles/Backfire Brawl
added.description: High Flying Hostiles: While escorting the Mind Core Cell to AAAnimus Campus, the AO are attacked by Masato Kazami and his Body Guards./Backfire Brawl: Philomena's attempt to refocus the Mind Core Cell's power backfires and the AO must fight their fellow employees inside the AAAnimus Campus.

added.title: Hostile Take Over/The Big Bounce
added.description: Hostile Take Over: After more unsuccessful attempts to harness Core Cell energy the AO must battle their own Bakugan with AAAnimus tech in order to save them./The Big Bounce: The AO confront Philomena with concerns about her control over the Core Cell energy and are fired in the most unceremonious of manners.

added.title: Despeguemos
added.description: De excursión en Cabo Cañaveral, el trío Tennyson presencia el lanzamiento inaugural de una nave espacial experimental, pero cuando Vilgax comanda la nave, Ben debe impedir que el villano use el transbordador como arma antes de que la cuenta regresiva llegue a cero.

added.title: Batalla en El Biggie Box
added.description: Ben y Billy Billions se enfrentan por un set de sumo exclusivo que se vende únicamente en el centro comercial más grande del mundo, isolo para descubrir que Simon Sez, de apenas seis años, lo compró primero! Así se desata una batalla dentro de una tienda que parece tenerlo todo excepto una salida fácil de encontrar.

added.title: Buen Viaje
added.description: Abordo del SS Pettigrew en su último viaje, Ben debe luchar no solo contra el mareo sino también contra Vapor Smythe, que se propone usar a sus criaturas mecánicas para hundir el barco moderno que remplaza al vapor... iy a sus pasajeros!

added.title: Juego Terminado
added.description: Unagami entra al mundo real y aterroriza a la ciudad de Ninjago mientras Jay, Zane y Pixal intentan evitar el desastre reuniendo a Unagami con Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: Los Ninjas están invitados a asistir a la fiesta de cumpleaños de la princesa Vania en la ciudad de Shintaro. Llevan al Maestro Wu que está deprimido.

added.title: En la Oscuridad
added.description: La princesa Vania revela una entrada secreta que conduce a una mina subterránea bajo Shintaro donde se guardan los oscuros secretos de la ciudad.

added.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
added.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

added.title: Las Dos Espadas
added.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

added.title: Pequena Escuela Madre
added.description: Bienvenidos a la Pequeña Escuela Madre, un lugar en la Tierra donde Gemas de todo el universo pueden aprender a vivir juntas pacíficamente. Pero hay una Gema que se rehúsa a asistir.

added.title: Consejos
added.description: Amatista ha estado ayudando a las Gemas de Pequeña Escuela Madre a encontrar trabajo, pero Steven no está seguro de su enfoque.

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: Azulejo
added.description: Steven cuestiona los motivos de una misteriosa fusión que de repente se presenta en su casa.

added.title: Fallo de tigre
added.description: Gwen se niega a que la presionen para elegir un sabor de helado que no quiere.

added.title: Una ninja justicia para Harold
added.description: El mundo de Harold queda de cabeza cuando sus compañeros declaran que Beth es la verdadera ninja de la clase.

added.title: El castigo de mi vida
added.description: Owen forma un nexo especial con Duncan después de que ambos se divirtieran mucho durante sus castigos.

added.title: Fragmentos
added.description: Steven se dirige al bosque para entrenarse con un poderoso mentor.

added.title: Rumbo al Planeta Madre
added.description: Steven acude a las Diamantes para pedirles consejos sobre cómo controlar sus nuevos poderes.

added.title: Todo Esta Bien
added.description: Steven insiste en que todo está bien.

added.title: Soy Mi Monstruo
added.description: No todo está bien.

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: Steven por fin está listo para avanzar.

added.title: Necesidad De Velocidad
added.description: De paseo por Yellowstone, Ben descubre el plan del rápido y furioso LaGrange para encontrar un tesoro enterrado bajo el parque nacional. Pero con una ayudita del géiser Viejo Fiel, Overflow logra empapar los sueños de LaGrange.

added.title: Omni-Truco
added.description: Ben debe interrumpir sus vacaciones en Portland cuando descubre un 11mo alien al luchar contra la mega criatura del Dr. Animal. Pero, como la lucha deja a su Omnitrix todo estropeado pasando por los 11 aliens, Max pide ayuda a un viejo amigo para que repare el Omnitrix, que es perseguido por otras fuerzas peligrosas, entre ellas un alien misterioso de la misma especie que el 11mo alien...iVilgax!

added.title: 'Twas the Fight Before Christmas
added.description: When Princess Morbucks tries to ruin Christmas for the children of the world, the Powerpuff Girls must save the day.

added.title: Nia's Balloon Blunder
added.description: When a parade balloon Nia is set to deliver flies away, Thomas helps Nia adjust her plans to get it back.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: When Percy loses Nia's parade flag before the big parade, Thomas helps them search for it before the event begins.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Mystery Boxcars
added.description: Kana is upset when she keeps running out of power, but a mystery scavenger hunt is just the thing to cheer her up.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Puddle Olympics
added.description: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

added.title: A Lot Like Lola
added.description: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her.

added.title: Mother's Day Madness
added.description: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

added.title: Takers Keepers
added.description: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want.

added.title: To Tell the Tooth
added.description: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

added.title: Once Upon a Rainbow
added.description: When Grumpy mysteriously loses his blue color in a far-off area of the Silver Lining, the Bears track down the cause: a creature called the Painter has lost the key to the magical paintbox that creates all the color in the area. Grumpy must recover the key to restore his blueness.

added.title: After the Klatternack
added.description: The Care Bears try to capture the Klatternack, a comical creature whose non-stop nonsense is annoying the local Whiffles. The Bears are joined by the ultra-serious Tracker, who has long been after the Klatternack himself. But despite their combined efforts, the wily creature continues to elude them - until Share realizes there is more going on than meets the eye.

added.title: Let the Fun Shine
added.description: Expert skateboarder Funshine tries to duplicate the in-the-groove fun Dibble has when she rides her little cloud like a skateboard, but he discovers along the way that having fun isn't always about a better skateboard or riding a cloud, it can be about trying harder at something and finally succeeding.

added.title: Valley of the Shamrocks
added.description: When Grumpy replaces mission navigator Good Luck with a computerized navigational gadget, Good Luck feels useless -- until he saves the Valley of the Shamrocks and is proclaimed a hero by the Whiffles, who don't want him to leave. He is torn between staying with the Whiffles and remaining with the Bears.

added.title: Some Luck
added.description: While the Bears are transporting a Whiffle Wizard to a distant meadow, Good Luck seems to have a run of bad luck. His belief in his own bad fortune causes him to lose confidence, causing ever more "bad luck." It's only when he understands that we make our own luck that his "luck" changes.

removed.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
removed.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

removed.title: El Hechicero Calavera
removed.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

removed.title: Animorfosis
removed.description: El trío Tennyson excava fósiles de dinosaurio, pero Ben no sabe que Vilgax y el Dr. Animal se complotaron para robar ADN alien del Omnitrix, pero, una vez extraído el ADN, Vilgax traiciona a su cómplice. Ahora Ben debe aliarse con el malvado doctor si quiere tener la oportunidad de derrotar al gran villano. Pero ¿puede confiar en el Dr. Animal?

removed.title: La Reina de los Munces
removed.description: Jay, Nya y Lloyd son guiados entre las minas de Shintaro por Murt, quien los lleva de vuelta a la Cueva de los Munces. A la Reina Munce le gusta Jay.

removed.title: Bombazobo Vive
removed.description: Durante un viaje de rutina al DMV, Max toma un examen de manejo para renovar su licencia. Pero cuando Zombozo, disfrazado, se apropia del papel del instructor, Ben se convierte en alienígena para detener al malvado y salvar el viaje familiar.

removed.title: Presentando a La Creatura
removed.description: Cuando Max se queda dormido antes de una doble función, Ben y Gwen se ven obligados a salvar el autocine solos. Ocurre que el malvado mago Hex da vida al monstruo de una película, que aterroriza a los espectadores.

removed.title: Juicio de Mino
removed.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

removed.title: Atrapagritos
removed.description: Cuando una caries obliga a Ben a ir al dentista, su día empeora aún más cuando el malévolo mago Hex usa un atrapasueños para materializar los miedos de nuestro héroe y los transporta con él a un lugar pesadillesco.

removed.title: Desastre en Mascota
removed.description: Frustrado su intento de conseguir una foto con cada mascota de vidriera, Ben y Gwen se escabullen de noche para tomarse su foto con el tótem del oso de madera... iy descubren que él y las demás mascotas cobraron vida!

removed.title: La Gran Caida
removed.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

removed.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
removed.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

removed.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
removed.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

removed.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
removed.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

removed.title: Return to Forever
removed.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

removed.title: Gwen 10
removed.description: Gwen gets her hands on the Omnitrix and all its powers and now Ben has to take a backseat as Gwen 10 battles Vilgax for control of the device.

removed.title: Food Around the Corner
removed.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

removed.title: Under Wraps
removed.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

removed.title: T.G.I.S
removed.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

removed.title: Grudge Match
removed.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

removed.title: The Unnaturals
removed.description: Ben learns that evil robots have replaced all the kids at the Little League World Series. And now they want to replace the President of the USA!

removed.title: The Return
removed.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

removed.title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
removed.description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!

removed.title: Return to Care-A-Lot
removed.description: Bluster and his bad crowd invade Care-A-Lot, determined to steal the Care-O-Meter and stop the Care Bears' mission of caring and sharing. To foil his plan, the Bears must rely on an unlikely ally.

removed.title: Volcano
removed.description: On a drive through the mountains, Blippi is nearly hit by a puff of smoke from a volcano vent! Curious about what makes a volcano erupt, Blippi and FETCH fly into the volcano. With some close calls, they watch Maggie the Magma Monster gobble up the floor and play a favorite game - The Floor is Lava!

removed.title: Snow Day
removed.description: The babies experience their first snowfall.

removed.title: Bruce Bunny
removed.description: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce.

removed.title: The Big Freeze
removed.description: The Bears investigate the mysterious transformation of a tropical valley into a winter wonderland of snow. To return it to its natural state, Funshine must follow Dibble's example and give up something he wanted for himself.

removed.title: Christmas in July
removed.description: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

removed.title: Snow-verload
removed.description: The Bears investigate the mysterious transformation of a tropical valley into a winter wonderland of snow. To return it to its natural state, Funshine must follow Dibble's example and give up something he wanted for himself, just as Bluster and his bad crowd invade Care-A-Lot! They're determined to steal the Care-O-Meter and stop the Care Bears' mission of caring and sharing. To foil his plan, the Bears must rely on an unlikely ally.

removed.title: Spin Out
removed.description: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy.

removed.title: Accidents Happen Boo Boo Song
removed.description: Ella falls over, but Heidi the Horse teaches her to get right back up again!

removed.title: The Joke is on Thomas
removed.description: When Thomas and Percy's plan to surprise Diesel goes awry, the two friends still manage to cheer up Diesel... just not in the way they expected!
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
removed.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

removed.title: The Last Laugh
removed.description: Disappointed when his friends don't laugh at his jokes, Funshine encounters the Laffinpuff, a magical comedian who grants Funshine's wish to make everyone think he's funny. But Funshine realizes it's no fun being funny when people laugh at everything he says, whether he means it to be funny or not. To get the wish rescinded, he must face the Laffinpuff in a grueling ordeal of slapstick humor.

removed.title: Pinecone Palooza/The Big Footed Cave Bird
removed.description: Grandma and Timmy are entering the Pinecone Art Show by carving a sculpture out of stone… that is, if they can learn how to carve./Ranger Nat is hiking and comes across the Big-Footed Cave Bird, and realizes it can't get back into her home.

removed.title: Squirrels
removed.description: Blippi and FETCH are going on a treasure hunt! For Squirrel treasure that is. Their new friend Sparky the Squirrel has her nuts buried all over the park and Blippi tries to remember where she buried them. Sparky remembers them all though and Blippi learns why squirrels bury their nuts.

removed.title: Overnight Stop
removed.description: Percy feels anxious about spending a night away from home during an overnight delivery with Thomas and Nia.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Super Screen Cleaners
removed.description: Thomas pretends to be a hero to help ensure the movie screen Nia's delivering arrives clean and pristine.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Say What?
removed.description: When Share magically has her voice stolen from her in a field of flowers, she and the other Bears must learn to listen so they can find her voice and solve the problem between the flowers and their Whiffle gardeners.

removed.title: Shadow of a Doubt
removed.description: Tweety sheds some light on what a shadow is.

removed.title: Classic Rock
removed.description: Batman thinks he's helping a homeless old man who is being mugged on the street only to discover that the man is a powerful wizard being chased by demons in disguise. It turns out the wizard is on a mission to save Shazam from the clutches of Black Adam.

removed.title: Follow that Space Cab!
removed.description: While Superman escorts his prisoner Mr. Mind between planets, he is attacked by Lobo who wants to collect a reward on Mind. Temporarily powered-down, Superman seeks Space Cabbie's help to get away from Lobo.

removed.title: Night of the Bat
removed.description: Superman and other Justice League members have to battle Batman when he gets possessed by an evil Djinn, Uthool, who is intent on using the JL power core to blow a crack in Earth.

removed.title: Abate and Switch
removed.description: When the JLA tries to stop the Brothers Djinn, the ghoulish trio are able to direct spells on our heroes by saying their names forcing them to disguise themselves as each other in order to foil the spells.

removed.title: Power Outage
removed.description: A ghoul known as Calythos possesses the Parasite in order to drain the Justice League of its powers and use that stolen strength to open a massive volcano.

removed.title: Mayhem in Mascot
removed.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

removed.title: Creature Feature
removed.description: When Max dozes off before a double feature, Ben and Gwen are left to save the drive-in by themselves as the evil magician Hex brings the movie monster "That" to life, and unleashes him on the unsuspecting moviegoers.

removed.title: Screamcatcher
removed.description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

removed.title: Locked Out Cold
removed.description: On the eve of a big holiday party, the Williams kids are locked out of the house, leading to a frantic search all over town for a spare key.

removed.title: Craig of the Street
removed.description: Craig visits his cousin, Bryson, and they go on a quest through the streets of New Jersey.

removed.title: Craig to the Future
removed.description: The Witches of the Creek use their mystical powers to give Craig and his friends a glimpse into the future.

removed.title: Paint That a Shame
removed.description: Leshawna creates a paint balloon fight to decide who gets to come with her to an amusement park.

removed.title: Snow Country for Old Men
removed.description: In an attempt to win the holidays, Chef brings snowmen to life to entertain the kids. But when they turn out to be evil, Chef and the kids have to jingle some bells.

removed.title: The Tree Stooges Save Christmas Part 2
removed.description: The kids accidentally destroy Chef's decorated Christmas tree. Scared this means they've ruined his Christmas, they go on an epic mission to replace his holiday treasures.

removed.title: The Tree Stooges Save Christmas Part 1
removed.description: The kids accidentally destroy Chef's decorated Christmas tree. Scared this means they've ruined his Christmas, they go on an epic mission to replace his holiday treasures.

removed.title: Me, My Elf, and I
removed.description: Duncan tricks Chef into taking the class to the North Pole in order to remove his name from the naughty list.

removed.title: Trouble Busters!/French Fry Wars
removed.description: Trouble Busters!: Now that the Awesome Brawlers are world famous Bakugan experts, they want to help people solve their Bakugan-related problems. When the world's quietest town is experiencing unexplained noises, the Awseome Brawlers are called in to get to the bottom of it./French Fry Wars: The Awesome Brawlers are arguing over who gets to eat the last french-fry. At first, each member makes a case for why they should to be the one to eat it. But the quarrel quickly escalates into trash talk and revealing secrets about one another. With everyone now upset, things take an unexpected turn.

removed.title: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call/Phantom Thief Ajit
removed.description: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call: An archeological discovery is made in Los Volmos. Exploration at the site is cut short, when a master thief and his apprentice attempt to steal the ancient Bakugan artifacts. When the Awesome Brawlers hear the news, they step in to thwart the thieves./Phantom Thief Ajit: An Ancient Bakugon artifact from an archeological discovery is placed in the Los Volmos Museum. The Awesome Brawlers are charged with guarding the artifacts from any further attempts thievery.

removed.title: Baku-Gear/Bakugan Rock!
removed.description: Baku-Gear: The Awesome Brawlers are excited over their discovery of Baku-Gear, and want to get some footage of it in action. While they're filming, an underclassman named Trey challenges Dan to battle. Who will emerge victorious in the impromptu battle?/Bakugan Rock!: Baku-gear has shown up twice for Dan and Drago and it's starting to eat away at the other awesome brawlers. It's time they take it into their own hands. When Lia and Wynton go up against the rockin' new brawlers in town, they show Dan and Drago that they are not the only one who can summon this cool new tool!

removed.title: Brawler Headhunting/Lightning's Entrance Exam
removed.description: Brawler Headhunting: As acting president of Kazami International, Shun is called upon to entertain another new young CEO Luca Schmidt, who's interested in doing business with the Kazami International. But Shun quickly realizes something is up when Luca tries woo him over to his brawling team - the Glanz Five. /Lightning's Entrance Exam: The Awesome Brawlers may be world famous heroes, but that doesn't mean they get out of going to school. They are still regular kids, doing regular kid things. But teachers may have something to say when Lightening decides he wants to join his buddies in the classroom.

removed.title: The Mysterious Boy/A New Power
removed.description: The Mysterious Boy: After stopping Tiko's rampage, the Awesome Brawlers have become world-famous heroes and Bakugan-mania sweeps the globe. With the Bakugan boom, brawling has been reinvented as a sporting game. In celebration of the Awesome Brawlers efforts, a tournament is being held in their honor. But the battles are quickly cut short when a rogue brawler and his golden Bakugan crash the event./A New Power: A Rogue brawler, Agit and his golden Bakugan have crashed the Awesome Brawlers party. Who is this brawler? How can he control a Golden Bakugan? Only one way to find out - Bakugan Brawl! Dan and Drago go head to head with the outsides to get to the bottom of it. Outmatched by their opponent, Dan and Drago get a little help from a new powerful weapon - Baku-Gear.

removed.title: Queen of the Munce
removed.description: Jay, Nya and Lloyd are led deep into the Mines of Shintaro by Murt, who brings them back to the Munce "Home- Cave" - a settlement deep in the mountain. There, complications arise when they meet the Munce Queen, Murtessa, who takes a liking to Jay.

removed.title: The Skull Sorcerer
removed.description: Separated from the others, Cole must trust his instincts and make the right choices to find his way to the surface to alert King Vangelis of the dangerous Skull Sorcerer.

removed.title: The Real Fall!
removed.description: An entire episode chronicles the ninja's most bizarre adventure yet: in which Cole, Princess Vania and Master Wu fall down a seemingly endless tunnel, into the bowels of Shintaro Mountain.

removed.title: Dungeon Party
removed.description: Having survived their fall into the mountain, Cole, Wu and Princess Vania befriend a motley group of survivors, called the Lowly, and are told the story of how they too ended up at "Rock-Bottom."

removed.title: Trial By Mino
removed.description: Separated from the others, Kai and Zane discover a party of Geckles who suspect them of being in league with the Skull Sorcerer, and bring them before their leader, Chancellor Gulch, who subjects them to a "Trial-By-Mino."

removed.description: The Bears are invited to live with a family of cavemen but things get rocky when the bears teach the family about television.
